⚡ SwiftUI Performance Optimization (Day 1)

SwiftUI is fast by design, but poor architecture can make it surprisingly slow.

Most performance issues come from:

Excessive body recomputation

Incorrect state ownership

Unstable view identity

Overly complex view trees

Understanding these patterns prevents laggy UIs and battery drain.

🧠 Performance Mental Model

SwiftUI works in three steps:

State Change
   ↓
View Recalculation
   ↓
Diffing Engine
   ↓
UI Update

Your job is to minimize unnecessary recalculations.

1️⃣ Keep body Cheap
❌ Anti-Pattern
var body: some View {
    let sorted = items.sorted()
    return List(sorted) { item in
        Text(item.name)
    }
}

Sorting runs every render.

✅ Correct
@State private var sortedItems: [Item] = []

.task {
    sortedItems = items.sorted()
}

Now sorting runs once.

2️⃣ Use Correct Property Wrappers

SwiftUI performance depends heavily on state ownership.

Wrapper	Impact
@State	Local state
@StateObject	Owns reference
@ObservedObject	Observes external state
@EnvironmentObject	Global invalidation
❌ Performance Bug
@ObservedObject var vm = MyViewModel()

Recreated every render.

✅ Correct
@StateObject var vm = MyViewModel()

Stable lifetime.

3️⃣ Stable Identity Is Critical

SwiftUI uses identity for diffing.

❌ Bad
ForEach(items, id: \.self)
❌ Worse
.id(UUID())

This forces full view recreation.

✅ Correct
ForEach(items, id: \.id)

Stable identity = minimal diffing.

4️⃣ Prefer Lazy Containers
❌ Bad
VStack {
    ForEach(items) { item in
        ItemRow(item)
    }
}

All views render immediately.

✅ Correct
LazyVStack {
    ForEach(items) { item in
        ItemRow(item)
    }
}

Views render on demand.

5️⃣ Avoid Large View Trees

SwiftUI diffing cost grows with view complexity.

❌ Bad
VStack
 └─ HStack
     └─ ZStack
         └─ VStack
             └─ Text
✅ Prefer Simpler Layout
VStack
 └─ Text

Flat hierarchies perform better.

6️⃣ Extract Subviews

Large views cause:

ViewBuilder explosions

Poor diffing

Slower compile times

❌ Bad
var body: some View {
    VStack {
        // 200 lines of UI
    }
}
✅ Correct
var body: some View {
    VStack {
        header
        content
        footer
    }
}
7️⃣ Use .task Instead of .onAppear

.task integrates with Swift concurrency.

❌
.onAppear {
    loadData()
}
✅
.task {
    await loadData()
}

This prevents repeated work.

8️⃣ Debugging Performance Issues

Use these tools:

Instruments
SwiftUI → Body Updates
Debug prints
print("body recomputed")
Xcode tools
Debug → View Hierarchy
